WEBVTT

00:06.007 --> 00:08.759
[indistinct conversation]

00:09.969 --> 00:11.762
[door closes]

00:11.971 --> 00:13.014
Woman, mumbling:
Is the door locked?

00:13.222 --> 00:15.016
Girl: Yeah.

00:15.224 --> 00:16.726
[woman mumbling]

00:18.311 --> 00:19.937
Girl: Okay, here.

00:20.146 --> 00:21.856
[woman mumbling]

00:22.064 --> 00:23.900
Woman: Now, lift me up.

00:24.108 --> 00:25.443
Girl: Okay.

00:27.528 --> 00:28.321
Girl: Are you okay?

00:28.529 --> 00:29.530
Woman: Mm-hmm!

00:29.739 --> 00:31.032
Girl: Can I help?

00:31.240 --> 00:33.201
Woman: Hm-mm-hm-mm.

00:33.367 --> 00:34.744
Girl: Tie it tight.

00:34.952 --> 00:38.039
-[woman mumbling]
-girl: Good?

00:38.247 --> 00:39.957
Woman: You're gonna
have to push me.

00:40.208 --> 00:41.709
- Push you?
- Mm-hmm.

00:41.918 --> 00:43.669
- You sure?
- Yeah, do it!

00:43.878 --> 00:45.546
- Okay.
- One...

00:45.755 --> 00:47.173
girl: Two, three...

00:47.381 --> 00:49.675
-woman: Four... aah!
-[tooth yanked]

00:49.884 --> 00:52.762
Girl: Some memories
are so vivid,

00:52.970 --> 00:56.891
they play over again and again
in your mind.

00:57.099 --> 00:59.310
Maybe because they scare you.

00:59.519 --> 01:03.147
Maybe because they remind you
that you don't always know

01:03.356 --> 01:05.274
when you're about to hit
rock bottom.

01:05.483 --> 01:06.651
[car leaving]

01:19.705 --> 01:21.082
Come on, Mom, let's go.

01:24.460 --> 01:26.712
Look, we'll go somewhere nice
like the beach.

01:28.130 --> 01:29.840
And we'll get beef tacos.

01:30.049 --> 01:32.218
You know, the crispy kind
with extra cheese?

01:34.929 --> 01:36.472
Are you coming or not?

01:38.724 --> 01:40.726
Mom, we have to get out of here!

01:40.935 --> 01:42.770
I heard you.

01:42.979 --> 01:45.106
Ruthie, what are we
supposed to do?

01:45.314 --> 01:47.900
I don't have a job,
I don't have any money!

01:48.109 --> 01:51.279
[sighs] Well, if you're
not going, I'm going,

02:07.962 --> 02:11.799
Ruthie, go! Hurry!
Before he comes.

02:12.008 --> 02:13.968
What are you doing
with the TV?

02:14.176 --> 02:16.345
I can sell it.
We're gonna need moving money.

02:16.554 --> 02:19.181
- Okay.
- Come on. Get the trunk.

02:21.267 --> 02:22.226
Go.

02:24.228 --> 02:25.438
Ohh!

02:25.646 --> 02:26.939
Push it.

02:27.148 --> 02:29.317
Okay, come on.

02:29.525 --> 02:32.236
Let's go. Go!

02:35.072 --> 02:37.533
Ruthie: I was the one
who always knew

02:37.742 --> 02:39.327
when it was time to leave.

02:39.535 --> 02:41.579
Eventually,
all of my mother's boyfriends

02:41.787 --> 02:43.539
turned out to be creeps.

02:43.748 --> 02:45.541
We did what we always did.

02:45.750 --> 02:48.294
We took what we could and ran.

02:48.461 --> 02:51.839
This was me... and my mom.

03:06.270 --> 03:08.481
- Get in the car.
- Hey!

03:08.689 --> 03:11.859
This your little girl?
You two look more like sisters?

03:15.529 --> 03:16.989
See you soon.

03:40.096 --> 03:42.515
- Where should we go?
- Hmm?

03:42.723 --> 03:44.975
Anywhere you want.

03:45.184 --> 03:47.061
Anywhere, anywhere.

03:47.269 --> 03:48.854
Where's Harvard?

03:50.564 --> 03:51.732
Boston.

03:53.192 --> 03:54.485
Too cold.

03:54.694 --> 03:56.445
I'll get you a coat.

03:56.654 --> 03:59.281
Mom, I'm 14.
I'm not going to Harvard.

04:08.374 --> 04:09.792
Okay.

04:10.000 --> 04:13.170
So, Boston.

04:13.379 --> 04:14.880
Why not?

04:15.089 --> 04:17.925
You know, maybe I'll become
a doctor.

04:18.134 --> 04:20.219
I was just thinking
the same thing.

04:20.428 --> 04:25.057
You know, Ruthie, you would make
a great doctor.

04:25.224 --> 04:26.642
I would go to you.

04:42.116 --> 04:43.492
<i>Mmm'!</i>

04:45.369 --> 04:46.912
So good.

04:47.121 --> 04:49.206
What are you doing?

04:49.415 --> 04:51.333
- Just one.
- Mom, you have fries.

04:51.542 --> 04:53.502
Those are mine.

04:58.174 --> 05:00.301
This is just like old times.

05:02.136 --> 05:04.805
Now, it's just you and me.

05:13.481 --> 05:14.940
Fuck.

05:15.149 --> 05:16.108
Fuck!

05:16.317 --> 05:17.943
Are you okay?

05:18.152 --> 05:19.653
Mom.

05:19.862 --> 05:21.363
What?

05:21.572 --> 05:23.699
Mother: Goddamn it!

05:28.162 --> 05:29.955
[door closes]

05:30.164 --> 05:32.708
- Mother: Is the door locked?
- Ruthie: Yeah.

05:32.917 --> 05:38.339
Mother: Right there.
Hold it. All right?

05:38.547 --> 05:39.965
Now, lift me up.

05:41.884 --> 05:43.260
- Ruthie: Got it?
-mother: Mm-hmm.

05:43.469 --> 05:44.637
Ruthie: Tie it tight.

05:44.845 --> 05:48.349
-[mother mumbling]
- Good?

05:48.557 --> 05:51.185
[mother groans]

05:51.393 --> 05:53.979
You're gonna have to push me.

05:54.188 --> 05:55.815
- Push you?
- Mm-hmm.

05:56.023 --> 05:57.149
Ruthie: You sure?

05:57.358 --> 06:00.361
-[mother groans]
- Okay.

06:00.569 --> 06:03.656
Ready? Three, two, one...

06:03.864 --> 06:05.908
- Aaah!
-[tooth yanked]

06:06.116 --> 06:08.661
Mom? Are you okay?

06:08.869 --> 06:09.995
[moaning]

06:10.204 --> 06:11.705
Come on, it's okay.

06:11.914 --> 06:13.791
Oh.

06:13.999 --> 06:15.334
It worked.

06:15.543 --> 06:17.169
- Come on.
- We got it out.

06:17.378 --> 06:19.755
We did get it out.
Come on.

06:19.964 --> 06:22.466
Ruthie: To me, the hanging tooth
felt like rock bottom.

07:01.046 --> 07:03.048
Ruthie: Here, aspirin.

07:05.009 --> 07:08.137
I got Red Bull.
It's cold. Here.

07:08.345 --> 07:10.264
Mother: Thanks.

07:10.431 --> 07:13.100
- Mother: Ahhh!
- Ruthie: Better?

07:13.309 --> 07:14.768
Mother: Ahh.

07:18.731 --> 07:21.483
Ruthie: We're gonna have
a big house,

07:21.692 --> 07:24.445
like at least three stories.

07:26.488 --> 07:28.115
And it's gonna be yellow.

07:29.533 --> 07:32.494
- With black shutters.
- Uggh! With a sunflower.

07:32.703 --> 07:35.080
- Uh-huh.
- I love it.

07:35.289 --> 07:38.459
And we'll grow the grass out
real long.

07:41.211 --> 07:45.925
And we have to have
a big pool, too.

07:46.133 --> 07:48.177
It's gonna be round.

07:48.385 --> 07:50.387
I can just picture it.

07:52.556 --> 07:54.391
And...

07:54.600 --> 07:57.144
I think our pool
should have a slide.

07:57.353 --> 07:59.939
Mother, whispering:
I love slides.

08:00.147 --> 08:02.358
And we can get those rafts.

08:02.566 --> 08:05.819
You know, the ones that have
a place to put your drink.

08:06.028 --> 08:07.821
Mother: Yeah.

08:08.030 --> 08:09.823
It's going to be awesome.

08:10.032 --> 08:11.367
I love it.

08:16.622 --> 08:18.499
I'm picturing it now.

08:23.796 --> 08:26.757
How come you never tell me
about your mom?

08:30.094 --> 08:32.388
How come you always ask?

08:33.764 --> 08:35.265
Because I wanna know.

08:39.102 --> 08:42.063
Well, I had a lot of moms.

08:42.272 --> 08:43.565
Lots of moms.

08:43.774 --> 08:45.901
What were they like?

08:54.618 --> 08:56.829
Sweetie, I don't wanna
remember that.

08:58.956 --> 09:01.333
I just wanna look at you.

09:04.294 --> 09:05.504
[sighs]

09:05.713 --> 09:07.297
You always say that.

09:09.258 --> 09:11.301
Like your feet.

09:11.510 --> 09:14.304
Ruthie: They're not cute.

09:14.513 --> 09:16.015
No!

09:16.223 --> 09:18.350
- Oh, my God.
-[Ruthie laughs]

09:18.559 --> 09:19.518
Wow.

09:22.396 --> 09:24.314
[sighs]

09:40.664 --> 09:42.166
Ruthie: I love you, Mom.

10:37.846 --> 10:40.390
- Ruthie. Ruthie.
- Huh?

10:40.599 --> 10:42.476
Wake up. Come on.

10:44.812 --> 10:45.813
Wake up.

10:48.065 --> 10:49.191
Come on.

10:51.318 --> 10:53.278
We can't be in this parking lot
all day.

10:57.491 --> 10:59.743
Ruthie: My mom didn't believe
in maps.

10:59.952 --> 11:02.579
She just followed the signs.

11:02.788 --> 11:04.957
And when the spirit hit her,
we pulled over.

11:52.171 --> 11:53.797
[thunder rumbles]

12:10.689 --> 12:13.066
- Ruthie: Do you have any gum?
- Uh, yeah, somewhere.

12:14.735 --> 12:16.445
[knock on door]

12:16.653 --> 12:19.114
Be out in a minute!

12:19.323 --> 12:21.158
[knocking continues]

12:24.077 --> 12:25.454
[knocking]

12:30.250 --> 12:32.920
- Trash.
- Bitch.

12:33.128 --> 12:34.421
Come on, Ruthie.

12:36.173 --> 12:38.133
[muffler rattling]

12:41.345 --> 12:44.681
Ruthie: You think that
the sprinkles have a flavor?

12:44.890 --> 12:46.558
-[muffler clangs]
- What was that?

12:46.767 --> 12:49.102
Mother: Oh, shit, what was that?

12:49.311 --> 12:50.812
Ruthie: Oh, my God,
we're on fire!

12:51.021 --> 12:52.522
Mom, pull over!

12:52.731 --> 12:54.524
Mother: Oh, my God,
oh, my God, oh, my God!

12:54.733 --> 12:56.485
Ruthie: No, Mom! Mom! Stop!

12:56.693 --> 12:59.279
Mother: Get out of the car!
Get your coat!

12:59.488 --> 13:02.574
00h, shit! Shit!

13:02.783 --> 13:05.035
Stand back! Shh-shh-shh!

13:05.244 --> 13:06.787
[sizzling]

13:06.995 --> 13:08.622
Shit.

13:10.540 --> 13:11.750
Fuck.

13:11.959 --> 13:14.795
Piece of shit car!

13:15.003 --> 13:16.880
This shit life!

13:17.089 --> 13:20.133
Why does everything in my life
keep breaking, Ruthie?

13:21.760 --> 13:25.264
Goddamn it.

13:25.472 --> 13:26.765
Fuck!

13:26.974 --> 13:29.059
[drill whirring]

13:48.954 --> 13:51.331
Excuse me, excuse me.

13:53.917 --> 13:56.420
Look, ma'am, we're, uh...

13:56.628 --> 13:59.006
We're looking at $650,
$700 here.

13:59.172 --> 14:00.299
That much?

14:00.507 --> 14:01.883
I'm afraid so, ma'am.

14:05.804 --> 14:08.307
My daughter and I are really
struggling to keep going.

14:08.515 --> 14:11.476
That'll about break us.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.355
Maybe there's something
we could do to work it out.

14:22.654 --> 14:25.157
Some sort of special deal.

14:28.535 --> 14:30.829
You thinking about
selling your car?

14:39.046 --> 14:40.839
Oh.

14:41.048 --> 14:43.258
Oh, um, sorry, ma'am.
Uh...

14:43.467 --> 14:46.386
I mean, the muffler alone's
gonna run you $500.

14:46.595 --> 14:49.473
I'll do what I can for you
on our end with labor.

14:49.681 --> 14:51.475
Save you a couple of bucks
that way.

14:52.893 --> 14:54.436
But, uh...

14:54.644 --> 14:57.272
It's the best I can do.

15:08.533 --> 15:11.953
[thumbing through money]

15:58.917 --> 16:00.585
I'm okay.

16:02.671 --> 16:04.131
Don't worry, Mom.

16:05.757 --> 16:07.467
It's gonna be okay.

16:13.515 --> 16:15.517
-[mother sighs]
- What are we gonna do?

16:21.273 --> 16:22.482
Same plan.

16:26.027 --> 16:28.947
We're just gonna...

16:30.532 --> 16:32.117
figure it out as we go.

17:00.187 --> 17:02.939
How does this place look
for breakfast?

17:03.148 --> 17:04.608
Looks closed.

17:04.816 --> 17:07.152
Ruthie, it's perfect. Come on.
You know what to do.

17:17.412 --> 17:19.830
[knocks on window]

17:37.265 --> 17:39.100
-[doorbell jingles]
- Come on in.

17:39.309 --> 17:40.477
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

17:40.685 --> 17:43.230
We've been driving for hours.

17:43.438 --> 17:44.689
We're starving.

17:44.898 --> 17:46.691
We don't really open
for a half-hour,

17:46.900 --> 17:49.819
but, lucky for you,
my Uncle Marty loves kids.

17:50.028 --> 17:52.697
Is she really your daughter?

17:52.906 --> 17:54.157
You two look more like sisters.

17:56.701 --> 17:57.869
[chuckles]

17:58.078 --> 17:59.162
You want an OJ?

17:59.371 --> 18:01.039
Ruthie: Oh, yes, please.

18:01.248 --> 18:02.999
Do you think she's --

18:03.208 --> 18:08.088
Waitresses have
very good hearing, you know.

18:08.296 --> 18:10.924
Thank you for inquiring
about between my legs.

18:11.091 --> 18:13.260
I'm sure if you got to know me,
you'd see

18:13.468 --> 18:16.054
that it's what's between my ears
that's more interesting.

18:16.263 --> 18:17.973
Can I have a cup of coffee?

18:18.181 --> 18:20.433
Server: Coming right up.

18:20.642 --> 18:22.602
So, where are you-all headed?

18:22.769 --> 18:23.895
Boston.

18:24.104 --> 18:26.439
Server: Oh, Boston!

18:26.648 --> 18:29.609
I've never been there, but
that's not far from New York.

18:29.818 --> 18:31.695
I've always wanted
to move to New York.

18:31.903 --> 18:33.738
Start a career on the stage.

18:33.947 --> 18:37.951
Of course, I'd love to see
"Grey Gardens" live just once.

18:38.159 --> 18:40.662
With the great
Christine Ebersole.

18:40.870 --> 18:42.330
You know Christine Ebersole.

18:42.539 --> 18:44.457
She came in here once.
I met her.

18:44.666 --> 18:45.834
Told her I loved her.

18:46.001 --> 18:47.961
She said...

18:48.169 --> 18:49.963
"Thank you."

18:50.171 --> 18:51.715
I said, "No problem."

18:53.925 --> 18:55.719
So, what can I get you two?

18:55.927 --> 18:57.804
Um... [clears throat]

18:58.013 --> 19:00.932
I want the French toast special.

19:01.099 --> 19:02.475
Oh, with fruit.

19:02.684 --> 19:04.394
Mother: I'll have
the pancakes and eggs.

19:04.603 --> 19:06.104
Oh, and home fries.

19:06.313 --> 19:08.023
- Oh, what about bacon?
- Oh, yeah.

19:08.231 --> 19:11.484
Bacon and two orders
of sausage.

19:11.693 --> 19:14.404
And".oh.
How about two of those muffins?

19:14.613 --> 19:15.447
Server: You got it.

19:23.079 --> 19:24.831
Mother: Can you keep
a straight face?

19:25.040 --> 19:26.750
- Ruthie: You can't do it.
-mother: You do it.

19:26.958 --> 19:28.293
No, you gotta go like this.

19:30.211 --> 19:33.590
Proud members
of the clean plate club.

19:37.344 --> 19:40.513
I understand you two ladies
enjoyed our blueberry muffins.

19:40.722 --> 19:42.223
Mother: They have
a lot of blueberries.

19:42.432 --> 19:45.268
Well, then they're
appropriately named, I think.

19:45.477 --> 19:47.937
Pam, wrap up a couple
of blueberry muffins

19:48.146 --> 19:50.732
for these ladies
to take with them, okay?

19:50.940 --> 19:51.941
On the house, of course.

19:55.320 --> 19:56.279
Thank you.

19:56.488 --> 19:57.697
Of course.

20:01.493 --> 20:04.120
Server: Here. Take your time
with this, no rush.

20:08.875 --> 20:11.169
Mother, whispering:
Don't look so guilty.

20:11.378 --> 20:13.880
Ruthie, whispering:
I'm trying not to.

20:14.089 --> 20:16.132
Let me tell you something,
Ruthie.

20:16.341 --> 20:19.594
They don't give two shits
about you.

20:19.803 --> 20:21.596
You don't have to be mean.

20:21.805 --> 20:24.641
They have jobs.
And houses.

20:27.477 --> 20:29.979
They'll survive
no matter what we do.

20:34.025 --> 20:35.777
So get your shit together.

20:39.864 --> 20:41.908
The door's unlocked.

20:42.117 --> 20:43.618
I'll be out in a minute.

20:47.455 --> 20:48.581
<i>Hey '</i>

21:05.765 --> 21:08.810
-mother: Did they see us?
- Ruthie: No.

21:14.107 --> 21:15.567
Oh!

21:18.278 --> 21:19.404
Shit!

21:20.864 --> 21:22.407
Ruthie: Where are you going?

21:23.575 --> 21:25.326
Go on.

21:25.535 --> 21:27.120
[engine revving]

21:27.328 --> 21:29.164
Come on, Mom, we have
to get out of here!

21:29.372 --> 21:32.000
Mother: It's not going, Ruthie!
It's not mov-- Shit!

21:32.208 --> 21:33.418
Ruthie: Hurry!

21:33.626 --> 21:36.588
Mom, you can't just go backwards
the whole time!

21:36.796 --> 21:38.757
Mom, what are you doing?

21:38.965 --> 21:42.510
Pull over!
Mom, you have to stop.

21:42.719 --> 21:44.345
Mother: Shit, shit, shit!

21:44.554 --> 21:46.055
It's not going, Ruthie.

21:46.264 --> 21:48.516
- Mom, please, don't freak out!
-[engine revving]

21:48.725 --> 21:49.809
Mom, stop!

21:50.018 --> 21:52.103
Chill out, please!

21:56.316 --> 21:57.984
Mother: Oh, my God.

21:58.193 --> 22:00.236
Shit, shit...

22:00.445 --> 22:01.988
It's okay.

22:04.741 --> 22:06.326
Mom, it's okay.

22:21.925 --> 22:24.010
What are you doing?

22:24.219 --> 22:26.596
Gotta go back to the diner.

22:26.805 --> 22:28.515
- That diner?
- Mm-hmm.

22:28.723 --> 22:29.599
Why?

22:29.808 --> 22:30.892
Ouch!

22:31.100 --> 22:32.644
Our car broke down

22:32.852 --> 22:37.106
outside of a diner
right after we ripped them off.

22:37.315 --> 22:38.900
If that isn't the Lord's
work working,

22:39.108 --> 22:40.360
I don't know what is.

22:44.739 --> 22:46.032
Grab my purse.

22:47.617 --> 22:49.327
Here.

22:51.496 --> 22:55.583
So, we'll just go in
and tell 'em...

22:55.792 --> 22:56.584
Yeah.

22:56.793 --> 22:58.962
Confess. Come on.

23:02.590 --> 23:04.592
Oh, great.

23:04.801 --> 23:06.594
I have the cops on the phone
right now.

23:06.803 --> 23:08.429
I'm sorry.

23:08.638 --> 23:10.223
Put yourself in my shoes.

23:12.183 --> 23:14.143
What would you expect me
to do?

23:14.352 --> 23:16.271
Mother: I don't know
if you've ever been hungry.

23:16.479 --> 23:20.441
I don't know what to do anymore
except keep running.

23:20.650 --> 23:22.443
But we can't,
because our car broke down.

23:22.652 --> 23:24.696
And we have nothing.

23:24.904 --> 23:28.449
I mean, you can go ahead
and call cops, that's fine,

23:28.658 --> 23:30.034
but they're just gonna
send me to jail

23:30.243 --> 23:32.370
and they're gonna send my kid
to Child Services.

23:32.579 --> 23:34.122
Do you know what Child Services
is like?

23:34.330 --> 23:36.040
It's rough!

23:38.126 --> 23:40.795
It's really shitty.

23:41.004 --> 23:42.422
My Uncle Marty has a bad heart,

23:42.630 --> 23:44.924
and a stunt like that,
you could have killed him.

23:45.133 --> 23:46.467
Shh, shh!

23:48.511 --> 23:49.929
I'm sorry.

23:52.974 --> 23:54.642
Sometimes...

23:57.228 --> 24:01.065
I do...
I make bad decisions

24:01.274 --> 24:03.651
to make up for some other
bad decisions,

24:03.860 --> 24:07.947
and I'm so sorry, I'm so sorry.

24:08.114 --> 24:09.908
- I just --
- You're a thief.

24:10.116 --> 24:13.119
Look, mister,
superheroes don't fly

24:13.328 --> 24:14.913
or look like Jesus.

24:16.122 --> 24:19.208
They drive broken-down cars.

24:19.417 --> 24:21.502
They take their kids with them
no matter where they go

24:21.711 --> 24:23.129
or how bad things get,

24:23.338 --> 24:26.549
and sometimes they make mistakes
just like anyone else.

24:28.718 --> 24:30.845
