01:29:51.136 --> 01:29:52.346
No, uh...

01:29:52.555 --> 01:29:55.391
- Sorry.
- That's okay.

01:29:55.599 --> 01:29:58.727
Yeah, that's some of the stuff
I didn't clean out of there.

01:29:58.936 --> 01:30:00.813
I just got
a bunch of old stuff in there.

01:30:01.021 --> 01:30:02.940
Hmm. You play chess?

01:30:03.148 --> 01:30:05.234
Yeah, a little bit.
Do you play?

01:30:07.236 --> 01:30:09.738
Yeah, I mean,
what I like about chess

01:30:09.947 --> 01:30:11.782
is you can learn
as you go along.

01:30:11.991 --> 01:30:15.494
You can't win just by only
making forward moves.

01:30:15.703 --> 01:30:17.955
Sometimes you have to
take a step back

01:30:18.163 --> 01:30:20.875
or even lose a few pieces
to move forward.

01:30:21.083 --> 01:30:23.252
I think you just
have to be patient.

01:30:23.460 --> 01:30:26.046
You know, that's what
they say about it.

01:30:26.255 --> 01:30:28.591
Okay, you can have
the first move.

01:30:36.140 --> 01:30:38.350
Hey, Ruthie.

01:30:38.559 --> 01:30:39.518
Hi.

01:30:39.727 --> 01:30:41.186
"Breakfast of Champions"?

01:30:41.395 --> 01:30:43.355
Rita: Thank you.

01:30:43.564 --> 01:30:45.441
It's a book, Mom.

01:30:45.649 --> 01:30:48.360
- Oh.
- Uh, I like both.

01:30:53.365 --> 01:30:55.784
- Good morning.
- Hey, Ruthie.

01:30:55.993 --> 01:30:57.536
<i>Hey '</i>

01:30:59.079 --> 01:31:00.539
What are you doing today?

01:31:02.374 --> 01:31:03.751
Not a lot.

01:31:07.254 --> 01:31:08.964
- Hey, Ruthie.
- Hey, Ruthie.

01:31:09.173 --> 01:31:10.382
Ruthie: Hey.

01:31:22.686 --> 01:31:25.731
[indistinct conversation]

01:32:12.569 --> 01:32:14.154
Rita: Ruthie, what's wrong?

01:32:14.363 --> 01:32:17.741
What are we doing in this house?
I can't take this anymore.

01:32:17.950 --> 01:32:19.326
Can we please get out of here

01:32:19.535 --> 01:32:21.203
and stop living
this suburban lie?

01:32:21.412 --> 01:32:24.915
Rita: Ruthie!
We're not going anywhere.

01:32:25.124 --> 01:32:27.501
We're not running away anymore.

01:32:27.710 --> 01:32:29.044
- God.
- Ruthie!

01:32:29.253 --> 01:32:31.296
I can't believe this little
fairy-tale romance

01:32:31.505 --> 01:32:32.965
you made for yourself.

01:32:33.173 --> 01:32:35.384
Couple of alcoholics
getting clean.

01:32:35.551 --> 01:32:37.052
And falling in love.

01:32:37.219 --> 01:32:38.429
Stop it, Ruthie.

01:32:38.637 --> 01:32:40.431
Mom, I'm not a little kid
anymore!

01:32:40.639 --> 01:32:43.434
- Rita, straining: Yes, you are.
- Ruthie: Get away from me.

01:32:43.642 --> 01:32:45.644
- Ruthie: Mom, get off
- Rita: Go to bed, Ruthie.

01:32:45.853 --> 01:32:47.980
- Rita: Stop it!
- Ruthie: I'm not going to bed!

01:32:48.188 --> 01:32:49.440
No!

01:32:49.648 --> 01:32:51.608
Ow, damn it!

01:32:53.318 --> 01:32:55.404
Ruthie.

01:32:57.364 --> 01:33:00.284
Bravo, mom, happy ending.

01:33:00.492 --> 01:33:02.786
- Is that what you think?
- Don't start crying.

01:33:02.995 --> 01:33:04.621
- I'm not gonna start crying.
- Good.

01:33:04.830 --> 01:33:06.498
'Cause I'm sick of that, too!

01:33:06.707 --> 01:33:09.460
Oh, good, I'm glad you're just
sick of everything!

01:33:09.668 --> 01:33:11.962
I'm really glad
you're sick of everything.

01:33:12.171 --> 01:33:13.547
You go from boyfriend
to boyfriend,

01:33:13.756 --> 01:33:15.132
and why is Lee different?

01:33:15.340 --> 01:33:17.468
- Because he's a good person.
- Why is he so different?

01:33:17.676 --> 01:33:20.012
I love him, Ruthie,
and he loves us.

01:33:20.220 --> 01:33:21.555
Because he fixed your teeth?

01:33:21.764 --> 01:33:23.348
Because people need each other,
Ruthie.

01:33:23.557 --> 01:33:26.852
-[Ruthie scoffs]
- Because he takes care of us.

01:33:27.061 --> 01:33:29.521
Just like I take care of you.
He takes care of us.

01:33:29.730 --> 01:33:31.148
Get off me!

01:33:31.356 --> 01:33:33.817
You can't tell me what to do!

01:33:34.026 --> 01:33:36.820
- Yes, I can, I am your mother!
- Well, you don't act like it!

01:33:37.029 --> 01:33:38.238
- Yes, I do!
- No, you don't!

01:33:38.447 --> 01:33:40.324
You have no idea
what I've done for you!

01:33:40.532 --> 01:33:41.825
You don't know about foster care

01:33:42.034 --> 01:33:44.912
because I made damn sure
you don't know!

01:33:45.120 --> 01:33:47.206
So, if you wanna go, go!

01:33:47.414 --> 01:33:50.667
- I will leave!
- Then leave!

01:33:52.795 --> 01:33:54.338
I'll go.

01:34:08.519 --> 01:34:10.646
[dance music playing]

01:34:10.854 --> 01:34:12.648
[laughter]

01:34:27.830 --> 01:34:29.832
Oh, my God!

01:34:30.040 --> 01:34:31.917
Thank you.

01:34:40.008 --> 01:34:42.427
[laughter]

01:34:42.636 --> 01:34:45.597
One, two, three.

01:34:48.684 --> 01:34:51.687
She's gonna be fine.
You gotta trust me about that.

01:34:51.895 --> 01:34:55.190
She's at that age where she's
feeling kind of independent.

01:34:55.399 --> 01:34:56.650
She's never done this before.

01:34:56.859 --> 01:34:58.569
She's never run away.
This is not Ruthie.

01:34:58.777 --> 01:35:00.487
Right, but she's 15 now,

01:35:00.654 --> 01:35:02.447
so she's gonna start doing
stuff like this.

01:35:02.656 --> 01:35:04.700
It's totally normal.
You did it, right?

01:35:04.908 --> 01:35:06.493
And I did it.
Come on.

01:35:06.702 --> 01:35:08.287
It's what kids do.

01:35:08.495 --> 01:35:09.830
I promise.

01:35:10.038 --> 01:35:11.707
Come here.

01:35:11.915 --> 01:35:13.542
Come here, gimme a hug.

01:35:15.919 --> 01:35:16.920
Come on.

01:35:17.129 --> 01:35:19.256
[music pounding]

01:35:38.901 --> 01:35:40.360
What?

01:35:41.820 --> 01:35:42.613
Um...

01:35:42.821 --> 01:35:44.323
She...

01:35:44.531 --> 01:35:46.491
She followed in after me.

01:35:49.453 --> 01:35:51.038
Trash!

01:35:52.581 --> 01:35:53.498
Bitch.

01:36:07.638 --> 01:36:10.474
[sobbing]

01:36:10.682 --> 01:36:12.768
[truck horn blaring]

01:36:33.455 --> 01:36:35.123
[knock on door]

01:36:37.209 --> 01:36:38.502
Okay.

01:36:38.710 --> 01:36:40.462
[cat mews]

01:36:41.964 --> 01:36:44.007
[knocking]

01:36:50.013 --> 01:36:51.473
Rita: Thank you, Pam.

01:36:51.682 --> 01:36:53.225
Pam, whispering: I'm gonna go
make some coffee.

01:36:53.433 --> 01:36:54.559
Rita: Okay.

01:37:02.734 --> 01:37:03.735
I'm sorry.

01:37:09.866 --> 01:37:11.159
I'm sorry, too.

01:37:17.207 --> 01:37:21.211
Sometimes I just screw up,
Ruthie.

01:37:21.420 --> 01:37:23.171
You know, I try to be
a good mom.

01:37:23.380 --> 01:37:25.924
I've always tried, but I never
really knew what I was doing.

01:37:26.133 --> 01:37:27.843
And when you were little,
it was just...

01:37:28.051 --> 01:37:29.720
it was a lot easier
because if you fell,

01:37:29.928 --> 01:37:31.596
you know, I knew how to fix it.

01:37:31.805 --> 01:37:35.559
Like I could just make
your boo-boo better, and...

01:37:37.144 --> 01:37:39.646
And now I don't always know
what to do.

01:37:41.648 --> 01:37:42.858
I know.

01:37:44.192 --> 01:37:45.277
[sighs]

01:37:47.988 --> 01:37:50.073
I love you, Mom.

01:37:55.203 --> 01:37:56.747
I love you, Ruthie.

01:38:02.169 --> 01:38:04.588
You're a big girl now.

01:38:04.796 --> 01:38:05.672
[chuckles]

01:38:05.839 --> 01:38:07.007
Yeah.

01:38:12.429 --> 01:38:14.556
I never realized before...

01:38:14.765 --> 01:38:16.016
What?

01:38:18.727 --> 01:38:21.396
You need me
as much as I need you.

01:38:25.525 --> 01:38:27.027
Ruthie.

01:38:29.321 --> 01:38:31.490
Honey, I need you more.

01:38:40.791 --> 01:38:42.334
Mom, that's my clip.

01:38:42.542 --> 01:38:43.752
You gave it to me.

01:38:43.960 --> 01:38:45.295
When did I give it to you?

01:38:45.504 --> 01:38:47.255
You said you didn't want
to wear clips anymore.

01:38:47.464 --> 01:38:48.882
I did not give it to you.

01:38:49.091 --> 01:38:50.550
Uh, this is my skirt.

01:38:50.759 --> 01:38:52.761
Yeah, but this was for a party.

01:38:52.969 --> 01:38:55.806
This was for... a night.

01:38:56.014 --> 01:38:58.183
My hair was in my face.

01:38:58.392 --> 01:39:01.520
I saw you using it before.
I just didn't say anything.

01:39:01.728 --> 01:39:02.604
Here.

01:39:04.439 --> 01:39:06.191
Yes, you can drive.

01:39:06.400 --> 01:39:07.776
Oh, my God!

01:39:07.984 --> 01:39:10.862
[upbeat piano music]
